=== 2.4 Softmax

The *softmax* function converts a vector of real numbers (logits) into a probability distribution — all values positive and summing to 1:

stem:[\text{softmax}(z)_i = \frac{e^{z_i}}{\sum_{j} e^{z_j}}]

For numerical stability, it is computed with a constant shift:

stem:[\text{softmax}(z)_i = \frac{e^{z_i - \max(z)}}{\sum_{j} e^{z_j - \max(z)}}]

Subtracting stem:[\max(z)] does not change the output (the constant cancels) but prevents overflow when stem:[z_i] is large.

In GPT, softmax appears in two places:
attention weights (to turn raw scores into a distribution over tokens, Chapter 6) and the final output head (to turn logits into next-token probabilities, Chapter 10).

