==== Example

Let stem:[z = [2.0, 1.0, 0.1\]]:

Step 1 — shift by max (2.0): stem:[[0.0, -1.0, -1.9\]]

Step 2 — exponentiate: stem:[[e^0, e^{-1}, e^{-1.9}\] = [1.000, 0.368, 0.150\]]

Step 3 — sum: stem:[1.000 + 0.368 + 0.150 = 1.518]

Step 4 — divide: stem:[[0.659, 0.242, 0.099\]]

The highest logit (2.0) captures most of the probability (66%), but no value is exactly 0.

